Coloration. In life, dorsal color purple, mottled with small yellowish spots, which are also scattered on the limbs and tail (
Fig. 1
). Ventral color generally pale, flank with small yellowish spots but not as bright as the dorsal ones (
Fig. 2
). In preservative, dorsal color generally black brown, and ventral color grey; small yellowish spots appearing as grey spots.

Larva. The following description is based on the two larval paratypes (for measurements see
Table 1
). Head depressed, and width smaller than length. Interorbital space smaller than internarial space. Lips distinct, no eyelid. Vomerine teeth rows arranged in a “ ” shape. External gills three pairs, gill silts flat and short. Limbs slender, fingers and toes flat, with black horny cover at tips. Tail high, smaller than SVL, tip of tail abruptly peaked. Dorsal fin, like a wave, originating at the half of the truck; tail ventral fin originating at the back edge of cloaca.

Coloration of larve. In life, dorsal color flaxen, mottled with black brown spots (
Fig. 3
). In preservative, dorsum brown, spots grey.
